GRIDIRON DYNASTY — ROADMAP
Last Updated: June 19, 2026
Repository: https://github.com/blakewhitney3163/Gridiron-Dynasty
================================================================================

TIER 1 — Core experience improvements
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Surface Trade Offers on Main Screen — incoming CPU trade proposals visible
  from the Home tab alongside news. Also expose a place for users to update
  their own team status (Buyer / Seller / etc.) directly from the home screen.

Cleaner Pick Selection in Trades — make the draft pick trading UI more
  discoverable. Current flow is functional but not obvious.

TIER 2 — Strategic depth
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Contract Negotiation Depth — multi-year offer counters, holdout mechanic,
  dead cap penalties on early releases. Contracts feel functional but not
  deeply strategic today.

Coaching Staff System — OC/DC coordinators with ratings that affect team
  performance. Hiring and firing adds another management layer.

Draft Combine / Deeper Scouting — measurables (40 time, bench press) that
  hint at hidden potential. Ties into the existing 25-point scouting system.

Schemes — offensive and defensive scheme selection that shapes team identity
  and influences sim output (run-heavy, pass-heavy, zone vs. man, etc.).

TIER 3 — Polish & replayability
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Team Editor — edit team name, city, colors, conference/division.

League Customization — expansion teams, relocation, custom team names.

In-Game Narrative / Play-by-Play — text play-by-play during simulation.
  Stats-only output today limits immersion significantly.

